{"body": "There's still a few things bugging me about MessageEncryptor:\r\n\r\n1) The output is not URL-safe, which limits it's use for e.g. verification codes in URLs.\r\n2) The ciphertext and initialization vector is doubly base64-encoded (because of MessageVerifier).\r\n3) If Ruby 2 and OpenSSL 1.0.1 were required, the authenticated cipher aes-256-gcm could be used instead of a custom authentication, which would be safer and faster. Also, it wouldn't need two keys.\r\n\r\nI guess there's not much chance of incompatible changes being pulled, is there?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16617714", "created_at": "2013-04-18T22:56:12Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10235#issuecomment-16617714", "updated_at": "2013-04-18T22:56:12Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10235, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jleis", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://identicons.github.com/1d7a05b07251ba147253c6714637891f.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/received_events", "gravatar_id": null, "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jleis", "type": "User", "id": 158182, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jleis/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e15fbd3543c151008f96"}, "id": 16617714, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10235"}
